== An IBM 305 is not an IBM 650 ==

The discussion of the capacity of an IBM 350 connected to an IBM 305 RAMAC repeatedly conflates the 305 with the 650. They are different machines, with different data representations.

The IBM 650 had signed 10 digit words, with each digit represented in [[Bi-quinary coded decimal|bi-quinary]], and represented character data as pairs of decimal digits. The 305 represented characters as 6 bits plus parity. In both cases the character coding used was influenced by the coding on the [[Punched card|Hollerith card]]. Similarly, the formatted capacity of the 350 disk is not in the same units as the formatted capacity of the 355; the first is in characters (six bits plus parity) while the second is in signed 10-digit words. The relevant manuals are all available at [http://bitsavers.org/pdf/ibm/305_ramac/ http://bitsavers.org/pdf/ibm/305_ramac/] and [http://bitsavers.org/pdf/ibm/650/ http://bitsavers.org/pdf/ibm/650/]. [[User:Chatul|Shmuel (Seymour J.) Metz Username:Chatul]] ([[User talk:Chatul|talk]]) 23:44, 18 September 2014 (UTC)

